Eleventh Avenue at the south east corner of west 37th Street.
February 1st, 1932
P.L.Sperr,

11th Avenue, north from W. 37th Street. View 1 details the east side of this thoroughfare while 2 and 3 emphasize the west side. Note in the latter the metal construction shacks at the N. W. corner of 38th Street. These are being utilized by the Lincoln Tunnel excavators. The institutional appearing buildings beyond are the 6 and 7- story plants of the New York Butchers Dressed Meat Company. These occupy the 38th to 39th Street frontage.

Views 1,2: February 7, 1932
View 3: August 31, 1934

11th Avenue, west side, from W. 37th to 38th Streets, showing various manufacturing structures and tenements. The latter appear in the center.
They bear No's. 459 and 461 11th Avenue.

Note demolition of tenements at the left which bore No's. 45961. In the center, mostlv obscured by box cars, is the metal shack that houses the Lincoln Tunnel shaft entrance.
